formatted_address: 48a, Jalan Eko Botani 3/2, Taman Eko Botani, 79100 Iskandar Puteri, Johor Darul Ta'zim, Malaysia
name: Node Pilates Studio

reviews.text:
The teachers are fairly good but this studio does not seem to be cleaned very much. There are dust balls and hair around the equipment.

Also, there are not many classes at convenient times such as lunch.
Zen feeling studio and nice sofa to sit on! Appreciate the free drinks and friendly instructors!

Wife goes 2-3 times a week.   I go once a week with the awesomely professional Alice. Studio has that pilates Zen feel.   New machines in great condition.  Consistent great stretch classes... that pulls you to your limits.

I enrolled in both Mat and Reformer classes. The instructor is friendly and goes out of their way to ensure each member feels comfortable, supported, and guided through every move, especially newbies like me. ðŸ˜ŠðŸ˜Š

Great cozy and friendly pilates studio in JB!  I have attended classes (both reformer and mat pilates) taught by different instructors (Hui Yeen, Alice, Louana and Kaili) and they are all awesome! Highly recommend this pilates studio to all pilates beginner or pilates enthusiast!
